{"TopicId":220647,"ForumId":201,"TopicTitle":"Moving The Camera In Blueprint Mode When F2 Is Enabled Breaks The Background","CreatedByName":"FluffyHood","CreatedById":231163,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T12:58:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FluffyHood","CreatedById":231163,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T12:58:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0windows 11 pro | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 7 5700X 8-Core Processor 3.40 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3050 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EDescription:\u003C/span\u003E \u003C/strong\u003ETrying to move the camera in blueprint mode in F2 mode will result in free camera movement breaking the background.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWorkaround:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E click the blueprint mode button to reset the camera, then click it again to leave blueprint mode\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImage:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?ex=655a050f\u0026amp;is=6547900f\u0026amp;hm=316\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002289.92\u0022 height=\u00221049\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1169336452056875088/1170707219730407515/image.png?ex=655a050f\u0026amp;is=6547900f\u0026amp;hm=31618ea2b5834d0435dff9789b4e8c878c8dc86b7de28ff569b1a7b2681e9649\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-05T13:08:55Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2023 01:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 5\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Emade title more clear, added workaround\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-05T16:44:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, had this too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RUD Everyday","CreatedById":228396,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-25T21:37:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor me it showed an empty grassy area\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hoovy","CreatedById":222026,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-07T00:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-10400 CPU @ 2.90GHz 2.90 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia GTX 1660 Super | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically, you get a different isometric orientation of the craft you are building if you turn off UI/UX while in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, and in the isometric mode, then rotate your camera. This will always happen, craft or not, so it definitely doesn\u0027t seem to be part dependent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI personally think it could be used to take good screenshots of crafts, so instead of removing this ability fully, something similar to what it does would be nice, i.e just make the background blue and let the user rotate their camera however they want in a more intuitive way, or get rid of the background and just have kerbin could be nice.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gZ7DBeC.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/gZ7DBeC.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vaff6lP.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/vaff6lP.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like those (except in the blueprint one, get rid of the lines, idk) could be really nice for screenshots I think, so just entirely fixing the bug may not be the way to go imo, but eventually something similar to this would be nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_12/20231206164247_1.jpg.7d11bc78d726d9239d27788087ee4e27.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ipslightbox=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=betterbugreport.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=[!AES128GCM[pmpdVR7IldSHMgicSZiGNjp8v5NNpP9NzBC%2BlPTEiN2KHuPEmd2QKleop/62p9xsrqFAwOraNnrQpOzzilhVQ9lwQjbjFiNA][b2651be7a23aede0bd357178][4e0a5e9d070b2b71092a9a667bdd6c19]]\u0022\u003Ebetterbugreport.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=craft.txt\u0026amp;fileKey=[!AES128GCM[ggPWPgObPqq6VIcO7at/kKlhD80Vf7pCikaXEIoQmY1UnLTAiwOYa0c3%2BmMvSsGrz0cLy4FVbmW8xq%2BovN4=][e0bb7000c4ae517a8d7bb9b2][b73be49dc97542ff6bcd52dde8c490f9]]\u0022\u003Ecraft.txt\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-07T19:42:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222026-hoovy/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022222026\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222026-hoovy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Hoovy\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-07T20:07:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBlender and Cura let you position the camera arbitrarily when in ortho mode and I assume the same goes for most other CAD software so I have no idea why the default behaviour here is to snap you out of ortho mode if you face away from one of the cardinal directions. Please don\u0027t fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-07T20:08:23Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2023 08:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 7\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Bej Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hoovy","CreatedById":222026,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-08T23:50:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224345742\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220647\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701978132\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/7/2023 at 12:42 PM, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222026-hoovy/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022222026\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222026-hoovy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Hoovy\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry I tried looking to see if this bug report already existed but couldn\u0027t find anything on it, but its probably because of what people call the mode, and saying different things\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224345747\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220647\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701979668\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/7/2023 at 1:07 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBlender and Cura let you position the camera arbitrarily when in ortho mode and I assume the same goes for most other CAD software so I have no idea why the default behaviour here is to snap you out of ortho mode if you face away from one of the cardinal directions. Please don\u0027t fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think it should be fixed in the standard sense, but something similar would definitely be appreciated, while making it easier to get in and out of\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}